snippet.textDisplay: I played this all the time as a kid. It still ranks as my favorite game of all time. I have so many memories relating and revolving around it. The second game “Fossil Fighters Champions” was just as good a game if not better. So when Frontier came out I was super excited, but alas, it wasn’t as fun to play, nor did it bring much nostalgia. I still want another fossil fighter game, but I don’t want it to be as bad a game as frontier.

Fossil Fighter: Champions (which was good but lost the quirky animation) and then another one I like to forget because they got rid of alot of dinosaurs, as well as put alot of importance on driving around in a jeep. Recommend trying Chapions since you liked the base fossil fighters.

snippet.textDisplay: LOVED this game, and nobody ever talks about it! I wish it was a little tougher, tho. You get Spinax from the start, and you never really have a reason to drop it from your team. I remember grabbing a Siezmo for a support to just obliterate the enemy's supports, which were often at a type disadvantage against Siezmo.

snippet.textDisplay: Fossil Fighters was literally my childhood!!!!! I followed that jumbled up timeline perfectly and I remember also getting stuck in that pyramid, so stupid but 10/10 trap. And I totally understand the frustration of those soft rocks that break with one smash. Also yes the skull made the whole dinosaur, but the limbs made it stronger, I would get so mad when I would have every single bone BUT the head. And there are sooooo many dinosaurs, its actually a really really cool game and I think it should go down in history lol
